From what we can see in the previous steps' computations, the market price decline results from the new company expansion. Now, we will compute the net present value of expanding the company's facilities. This will assist us in determining the company's future earnings growth. This is computed as follows: 

 $$\begin{aligned}
\text{NPV}&={\text{-\$30 million+[(6,468,750$\times$\$62.66)-(6,000,000$\times$\$64.00)] }}\\[5pt]
&={\textbf{-\$8,668,125.00}}
\end{aligned}$$ 

**The NPV of the company expansion is -\$8,668,125.00.**
